title: For Sale:  Springfield M1 Garand 30-06 Rifle
location: New Mexico, New Mexico, United States
postcontent: This is a good condition US Springfield Armory, M1, 30-06 caliber, Garand rifle. The receiver on this C.A.I. Import was manufactured in December, 1954. The 24" barrel has a good bore and chamber. The parkerizing is good with the usual wear and use marks. The wood stock has been refinished, but is free from cracks or splits. As with most re-arsenaled import Garands, this rifle has a mixture of parts from different manufacturers, some wartime and some post war. The following parts are Springfield Armory manufacture: Trigger housing, receiver, operating rod (radius cut), and the barrel. The hammer is Winchester. The safety is Harrington & Richardson, and the bolt is International Harvester. We have not attempted to identify the rest of the parts. This is a solid, affordable, Garand rifle, which is becoming harder and harder to find. Should be a nice shooter.
